<subSubSection id="CA697FDC90F42684B81ECC4EDD66CCC2" pageId="0" pageNumber="83231" type="notes">
<paragraph id="9B85AF97A29DBBAE07185BBD65B50857" pageId="0" pageNumber="83231">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph id="29B283E8BC2CE4DE6BAF9367F47E0A76" pageId="0" pageNumber="83231">
First record for Bulgaria. 
<emphasis id="207B48065A05D717124DD79401C551ED" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83231">Northern Black Sea coast</emphasis>
: Varna, Morska gradina, 04.viii.2016, 2♂♂ and 1♀; Aksakovo vill., Pobiti kamani loc., 03.viii.2016, 5♂♂, 3♀♀ and 1 nymph; 
<emphasis id="156A6148053B963005074E11EC95C03A" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83231">Southern Black Sea coast</emphasis>
: Sinemorec vill., the mouth of Veleka River, 15.viii.2010, 1♂; Atia vill., 22.viii.2016, 1♂; 
<emphasis id="CAFA03166ABCB1E92E047FB4C657CC80" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83231">Strandzha Mt</emphasis>
: Pismenovo vill., 12.viii.2021, 1♂ (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="BDDC08D8A243ECF409E73E5DCA1186D1" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F7727403" captionText="Figure 6. Latilica maculipes (Melichar, 1906) - Bulgaria, Varna" figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e83231.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/653963" pageId="0" pageNumber="83231">6</figureCitation>
). Detailed occurrence data: 
<bibRefCitation id="6C1A08EC222A0727B73DDF808336B711" author="Gjonov, I." journalOrPublisher="Annals of the Upper Silesian Museum in Bytom. Entomology" pageId="0" pageNumber="83231" refId="B7727581" refString="Gjonov, I., 2022. new_fulgoromorpha_records_bulgaria_2022. In: Biodiversity Data Journal. Occurrence dataset." title="new _ fulgoromorpha _ records _ bulgaria _ 2022" volumeTitle="Biodiversity Data Journal. Occurrence dataset." year="2022">Gjonov (2022)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7ACE5FB9B45D0A67D9520B8FB2FAAD31" pageId="0" pageNumber="83231">
<emphasis id="FC5FE66F3FFA2804760E5ACF3657AA8E" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83231">Red Lists</emphasis>
